The plus symbol is a reserved character according [RFC3986][1] which is the standard specification for URIs and it is used to represent a space, therefore, if you want to use it in your URL as literally the &quot;+&quot; character instead of a space, you need to encode it so it looks like:

https://example.com/entity?sort_by=%2Bproperty

In ASP.NET Core you can encode / decode URL&#39;s as follows:

    using System.Net;

    string url = &quot;https://example.com/entity?sort_by=+property&quot;;

    string encodedUrl = WebUtility.UrlEncode(url);
    string decodedUrl = WebUtility.UrlEncode(encodedUrl);

See [here][2] for more info about URL encoding.


  [1]: https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3986
  [2]: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Percent-encoding

