And if the question would be only the title, *Addition of even fibonacci numbers* (let&#39;s say, *n* of them), pure mathematics could do the job, using Binet&#39;s formula (described in @Silerus&#39; [answer](https://stackoverflow.com/a/57935525/7916438)) and the fact that it is an `(a^n-b^n)/c` thing, where `a^n` and `b^n` are geometric sequences, every 3rd of them also being a geometric sequence, `(a^3)^n`, and the [sum of geometric sequences](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Geometric_progression#Geometric_series) has a simple, closed form (if the series is `a*r^n`, the sum is `a*(1-r^n)/(1-r)`).

